        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer493860" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18306887239171675978">This is a really good mix of<br/><br/>1) stylistically lithe prose, spontaneously beautiful and quirky, stream-of-consciousness without the cerebral aspect that turn some off to it (not that I mind that but...) and<br/><br/>2) intensely desperately human experience. A woman looks back on her life, as it has passed through the Spanish Civil War. Sounds bleak but an entire life, with everything in crisp detail, fits in.<br/><br/>Quite simply lovely and stunning, and every time i find a copy I buy it so I can give it away to an</span>
  <span id="freeText18306887239171675978" style="display:none">This is a really good mix of<br /><br />1) stylistically lithe prose, spontaneously beautiful and quirky, stream-of-consciousness without the cerebral aspect that turn some off to it (not that I mind that but...) and<br /><br />2) intensely desperately human experience. A woman looks back on her life, as it has passed through the Spanish Civil War. Sounds bleak but an entire life, with everything in crisp detail, fits in.<br /><br />Quite simply lovely and stunning, and every time i find a copy I buy it so I can give it away to another friend or family member who would never read it otherwise.<br /><br />This is one of the books I would take with me into exile and reread once yearly for the rest of my life.</span>
