  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1555890137" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1555890137" />
    <a title="Elizabeth (Alaska)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2026178-elizabeth-alaska"><img alt="Elizabeth (Alaska)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1304966095p2/2026178.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1555890137?book_show_action=true">Jun 15, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elizabeth (Alaska)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elizabeth (Alaska)" href="/user/show/2026178-elizabeth-alaska">Elizabeth (Alaska)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2026178-elizabeth-alaska?shelf=from-friends">from-friends</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2026178-elizabeth-alaska?shelf=mid-20th-century">mid-20th-century</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2026178-elizabeth-alaska?shelf=20th-c-women-read">20th-c-women-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2026178-elizabeth-alaska?shelf=women">women</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2026178-elizabeth-alaska?shelf=europe-other">europe-other</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1555890137" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14852651295763103323">This is not an autobiographical novel, but the whole of it seems to come from the author&apos;s experience. There is a very good Translator&apos;s Note prefacing this edition, written in 1980. He gives a brief historical background, and I quote just two sentences. <blockquote>Catalan is a language spoken by approximately seven million people ... Catalans were on the losing side in the Spanish Civil War, and immediately afterwards were forbidden to speak their language outside the home.</blockquote>This is a relatively short novel</span>
  <span id="freeText14852651295763103323" style="display:none">This is not an autobiographical novel, but the whole of it seems to come from the author's experience. There is a very good Translator's Note prefacing this edition, written in 1980. He gives a brief historical background, and I quote just two sentences. <blockquote>Catalan is a language spoken by approximately seven million people ... Catalans were on the losing side in the Spanish Civil War, and immediately afterwards were forbidden to speak their language outside the home.</blockquote>This is a relatively short novel, but I took more time with it than the page length would normally warrant. It is written in the first person. Some might characterize much of it as stream of consciousness. At the very least there are sections with numerous run on sentences. I didn't have any trouble understanding what Natalie was saying, rather it was hard to get a rhythm. Sometimes she was calm, others upset and nervous, and I didn't perceive the changes as quickly as I might have.<br /><br />Again referencing the Translator's Note: <blockquote>In a sense, <i>The Time of the Doves</i> is the story of most Spaniards during the 1930s and 1940s. But more profoundly, it explores what it feels like to be an ordinary woman in a Mediterranean country.</blockquote> I expected more to take place during the war. I even began to wonder if I had misunderstood the time period. And then, at the exact halfway mark - blam, we were all civilians in Barcelona while chaos reigned elsewhere. The next 40 or so pages are some of the best writing about what it means to be in a city during a civil war and that is cut off from supplies of all kinds, especially food, and where the able bodied men are elsewhere. I have to admit that without this section this book might not be worth a recommendation. It turns a low 3-star book into a mid- to high- 4 star book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14852651295763103323" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


